description:

Yet it is a good way of pushing someone who may not have been thinking about acquiring a certain product to consider it and then even take the step towards a purchase.

There is a fine line to walk between being overly descriptive and being too vague. Take the following sentence (taking from a website for a hotel in New York), for example, “Techno-glam energy surges through the one-bedroom Fantastic Suite in a bolt of cool electric blue, sparkling with Times Square energy in your own urban sanctuary atop the dazzling Broadway lights.” A description like this might make one sceptical more than interested. Can something really be so fantastical? On the other hand, a product that has too little information might make you wonder if there might be something wrong with the product and that’s why so little is said about it.

To know what type of product descriptions to use in your electronic product catalogue, you need to know to what type of customer you are appealing to.

short_description:
SQP311 – Low noise triple fixed displacement vane pumps

The SQP series are low-noise vane pumps offered in single, double, or triple pumps, with 4 frame sizes, 16 series, and 31 models of different discharge displacements. The wide extent of this range allows users to select the optimum combination of discharge displacements for their circuits, leading to an energy efficient system.

  • Lower noise – Offers very quiet and soft operational noise levels
  • Greater flexibility – Multiple pump combinations of different displacements permits simpler circuit design compared to systems using one large displacement pump and provides greater flexibility in circuit design with low noise levels
  • Maintenance friendly – Rotating element in cartridge kit form allows simple maintenance

description:
One might not think that something as trivial as a description of a product could mean the difference between someone buying or not. Yet it is a good way of pushing someone who may not have been thinking about acquiring a certain product to consider it and then even take the step towards a purchase.

There is a fine line to walk between being overly descriptive and being too vague. Take the following sentence (taking from a website for a hotel in New York), for example, “Techno-glam energy surges through the one-bedroom Fantastic Suite in a bolt of cool electric blue, sparkling with Times Square energy in your own urban sanctuary atop the dazzling Broadway lights.” A description like this might make one sceptical more than interested. Can something really be so fantastical? On the other hand, a product that has too little information might make you wonder if there might be something wrong with the product and that’s why so little is said about it.

To know what type of product descriptions to use in your electronic product catalogue, you need to know to what type of customer you are appealing to.

name: F11-SQP4-38-86C2-18 –  Fixed Displacement Low Noise Single Pump
description:
The SQP series are low-noise vane pumps offered in single,double, or triple pumps, with 4 frame sizes, 16 series and 31models of different discharge displacements. The wide extent of this range allows users to select the optimum combination of discharge displacements for their circuits, leading to an energy efficient system.

  • Offers very quiet and soft operational noise levels.
  • Multiple pump combinations of differing displacements permits simpler circuit design compared to systems using one large displacement pump and provides greater flexibility in circuit design with the benefit of low noise levels.
  • Rotating element is in cartridge kit form which allows simple maintenance.
short_description: SQP4 Series Pump

name: Config Legend-100AC-Red-Lorem Ipsum Sub1-20B
description:
The SQP series are low-noise vane pumps offered in single,double, or triple pumps, with 4 frame sizes, 16 series and 31models of different discharge displacements. The wide extent of this range allows users to select the optimum combination of discharge displacements for their circuits, leading to an energy efficient system.

  • Offers very quiet and soft operational noise levels.
  • Multiple pump combinations of differing displacements permits simpler circuit design compared to systems using one large displacement pump and provides greater flexibility in circuit design with the benefit of low noise levels.
  • Rotating element is in cartridge kit form which allows simple maintenance.

name: SQP311 Series – Fixed Displacement Low Noise Triple Pumps
description:
SQP311 – Low noise triple fixed displacement vane pumps

The SQP series are low-noise vane pumps offered in single, double, or triple pumps, with 4 frame sizes, 16 series, and 31 models of different discharge displacements. The wide extent of this range allows users to select the optimum combination of discharge displacements for their circuits, leading to an energy efficient system.

  • Lower noise – Offers very quiet and soft operational noise levels
  • Greater flexibility – Multiple pump combinations of different displacements permits simpler circuit design compared to systems using one large displacement pump and provides greater flexibility in circuit design with low noise levels
  • Maintenance friendly – Rotating element in cartridge kit form allows simple maintenance

Note – All standard options are omitted from the product model number.

Hydraulic fluid

  • Standard – Mineral oil-based fluid
  • F11 – Water glycol-based fluid

Shaft end pump displacement code – 25, 30, 32, 38

Middle pump displacement code – 4, 5, 8, 11, 12

Cover end pump displacement code – 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8

Shaft end configuration (Parallel sq. key) – 86

Shaft end delivery port position (viewed from cover end)

  • A – Opposite suction port
  • B – 90° Counterclockwise from suction port
  • C – Inline with suction port
  • D – 90° Clockwise from suction port

Middle pump delivery port position (viewed from cover end)

  • A – 135° Counterclockwise from suction port
  • B – 45° Counterclockwise from suction port
  • C – 45° Clockwise from suction port
  • D – 135° Clockwise from suction port

Cover end delivery port position (viewed from cover end)

  • A – 135° Counterclockwise from suction port
  • B – 45° Counterclockwise from suction port
  • C – 45° Clockwise from suction port
  • D – 135° Clockwise from suction port

Pump mounting

  • Standard – Flange mounting
  • Foot mounting – Delivery port position (as viewed from shaft end)
    • 2 – Up (12 o’clock)
    • 23 – Right (3 o’clock)
    • 26 – Down (6 o’clock)
    • 29 – Left (9 o’clock)

Rotation (viewed from shaft end)

  • Standard – Clockwise
  • LH – Counterclockwise

  • Maintenance friendly – Rotating element in cartridge kit form allows simple maintenance

name: TEST311 Series – Fixed
description:
SQP311 – Low noise triple fixed displacement vane pumps

The SQP series are low-noise vane pumps offered in single, double, or triple pumps, with 4 frame sizes, 16 series, and 31 models of different discharge displacements. The wide extent of this range allows users to select the optimum combination of discharge displacements for their circuits, leading to an energy efficient system.

  • Lower noise – Offers very quiet and soft operational noise levels
  • Greater flexibility – Multiple pump combinations of different displacements permits simpler circuit design compared to systems using one large displacement pump and provides greater flexibility in circuit design with low noise levels
  • Maintenance friendly – Rotating element in cartridge kit form allows simple maintenance

Note – All standard options are omitted from the product model number.

Hydraulic fluid

  • Standard – Mineral oil-based fluid
  • F11 – Water glycol-based fluid

Shaft end pump displacement code – 25, 30, 32, 38

Middle pump displacement code – 4, 5, 8, 11, 12

Cover end pump displacement code – 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8

Shaft end configuration (Parallel sq. key) – 86

Shaft end delivery port position (viewed from cover end)

  • A – Opposite suction port
  • B – 90° Counterclockwise from suction port
  • C – Inline with suction port
  • D – 90° Clockwise from suction port

Middle pump delivery port position (viewed from cover end)

  • A – 135° Counterclockwise from suction port
  • B – 45° Counterclockwise from suction port
  • C – 45° Clockwise from suction port
  • D – 135° Clockwise from suction port

Cover end delivery port position (viewed from cover end)

  • A – 135° Counterclockwise from suction port
  • B – 45° Counterclockwise from suction port
  • C – 45° Clockwise from suction port
  • D – 135° Clockwise from suction port

Pump mounting

  • Standard – Flange mounting
  • Foot mounting – Delivery port position (as viewed from shaft end)
    • 2 – Up (12 o’clock)
    • 23 – Right (3 o’clock)
    • 26 – Down (6 o’clock)
    • 29 – Left (9 o’clock)

Rotation (viewed from shaft end)

  • Standard – Clockwise
  • LH – Counterclockwise

The SQP series are low-noise vane pumps offered in single, double, or triple pumps, with 4 frame sizes, 16 series, and 31 models of different discharge displacements. The wide extent of this range allows users to select the optimum combination of discharge displacements for their circuits, leading to an energy efficient system.

  • Lower noise – Offers very quiet and soft operational noise levels
  • Greater flexibility – Multiple pump combinations of different displacements permits simpler circuit design compared to systems using one large displacement pump and provides greater flexibility in circuit design with low noise levels
  • Maintenance friendly – Rotating element in cartridge kit form allows simple maintenance

Note – All standard options are omitted from the product model number.

Hydraulic fluid

  • Standard – Mineral oil-based fluid
  • F11 – Water glycol-based fluid

Shaft end pump displacement code – 25, 30, 32, 38

Middle pump displacement code – 4, 5, 8, 11, 12

Cover end pump displacement code – 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8

Shaft end configuration (Parallel sq. key) – 86

Shaft end delivery port position (viewed from cover end)

  • A – Opposite suction port
  • B – 90° Counterclockwise from suction port
  • C – Inline with suction port
  • D – 90° Clockwise from suction port

Middle pump delivery port position (viewed from cover end)

  • A – 135° Counterclockwise from suction port
  • B – 45° Counterclockwise from suction port
  • C – 45° Clockwise from suction port
  • D – 135° Clockwise from suction port

Cover end delivery port position (viewed from cover end)

  • A – 135° Counterclockwise from suction port
  • B – 45° Counterclockwise from suction port
  • C – 45° Clockwise from suction port
  • D – 135° Clockwise from suction port

Pump mounting

  • Standard – Flange mounting
  • Foot mounting – Delivery port position (as viewed from shaft end)
    • 2 – Up (12 o’clock)
    • 23 – Right (3 o’clock)
    • 26 – Down (6 o’clock)
    • 29 – Left (9 o’clock)

Rotation (viewed from shaft end)

  • Standard – Clockwise
  • LH – Counterclockwise

MHT70/35/35-R1-15-JA-S123 – High torque low speed vane motors (Multi-Torque)
description:
• Special switching valves enables easy switching from low speed high torque to high speed low torque.
  • Balanced type vane motor provides wide range of speeds and torques.
  • Compact with large torque output.
  • Smooth, stable low speeds even at 10 rpm.
  • Compact design which eliminates need for gear boxes and reduction gears.

Full torque displacement code – 70, 90, 150, 190, 250, 380, 500, 750, 880, 1000

Partial torque displacement code – 35/35, 45/45, 75/75, 95/95, 125/125, 190/190, 250/250, 375/250, 625/500/375, 690/660/470, 750/500

Special switching valve

  • Standard – No switching valve
  • 8, 9 – Switching valve

name: DG4VL-3-0BL-M-PK2-H-7-56 – Low-holding current solenoid operated directional control valves
description:
DG4VL-3 – Low-holding current solenoid operated directional control valves

  • Energy-saving solenoid valve features reduced power consumption after switching (energized condition)
  • Integrated solid-state relay. Valve can be directly driven by connecting signal terminal to PLC, etc.
  • Mounting – 3 – ISO 4401-03

Note – All standard options are omitted from the product model number.

 

Hydraulic fluid

  • Standard – mineral oil-based fluid, water glycol-based fluid

Spool positions/conditions – 0, 2, 3, 6, 7, 24, 31

Spool/spring arrangements

  • A – Spring offset, A type (2 position, single solenoid)
  • B – Spring offset, B type (2 position, single solenoid)
  • C – Spring centered (3 position, double solenoid)
  • N – No spring detented (2 position, double solenoid)

Solenoid assembly orientation

  • Standard (energized P to B, A to T)
  • L – Left hand build (energized P to A, B to T)

Electrical wiring (configuration, wiring connection port thread size)

  • P – Plug-in type conduit box, G 1/2

Contact point input type (power, signal terminal connections)

  • K2 – Sink connection, 3 wire (fine current control)
  • E2 – Source connection, 3 wire (fine current control)
  • DE2 – Source connection, 2 wire (power ON/OFF control)

Voltage

  • H – DC24V

Allowable tank port back pressure

  • 7 – 20.6MPa

Port Options

Available in both no port orifices (standard) and varying port orifice sizes.  If you need a specific port, please write your request in the text box or contact us.

  • Standard – No port orifices

name: DG4VL-3 Series – Low-holding current solenoid operated directional control valves
description:
DG4VL-3 – Low-holding current solenoid operated directional control valves

  • Energy-saving solenoid valve features reduced power consumption after switching (energized condition)
  • Integrated solid-state relay. Valve can be directly driven by connecting signal terminal to PLC, etc.
  • Mounting – 3 – ISO 4401-03

Note – All standard options are omitted from the product model number.

Hydraulic fluid

  • Standard – mineral oil-based fluid, water glycol-based fluid

Spool positions/conditions – 0, 2, 3, 6, 7, 24, 31

Spool/spring arrangements

  • A – Spring offset, A type (2 position, single solenoid)
  • B – Spring offset, B type (2 position, single solenoid)
  • C – Spring centered (3 position, double solenoid)
  • N – No spring detented (2 position, double solenoid)

Solenoid assembly orientation

  • Standard (energized P to B, A to T)
  • L – Left hand build (energized P to A, B to T)

Electrical wiring (configuration, wiring connection port thread size)

  • P – Plug-in type conduit box, G 1/2

Contact point input type (power, signal terminal connections)

  • K2 – Sink connection, 3 wire (fine current control)
  • E2 – Source connection, 3 wire (fine current control)
  • DE2 – Source connection, 2 wire (power ON/OFF control)

Voltage

  • H – DC24V

Allowable tank port back pressure

  • 7 – 20.6MPa

Port Options

Available in both no port orifices (standard) and varying port orifice sizes.  If you need a specific port, please write your request in the text box or contact us.

  • Standard – No port orifices
